description.narrative: UNICEF supported the strengthening of teacher training with particular focus on remedial education, multigrade management, gender, disability inclusion, and digital education. Overall, 7,283 teachers and supervisors benefited from capacity building interventions focusing on pedagogical skills and learning outcomes. 242,232 learners in 1,443 schools,predominantly from vulnerable and underserved communities,received individual learning materials. Key innovations included the introduction of learning corners in primary schools and of targeted remedial education interventions. Overall, 177,450 children, adolescents and youths also participated in skills development programmes for learning, personal empowerment, active citizenship and/or employability. UNICEF also initiated support for implementing the bilingual education strategy. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:03/02/2022
